text: Ângela Moraes (born 15 October 1972) is a Brazilian female volleyball player, who played as a middle blocker. She was part of the Brazil women's national volleyball team at the 1999 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Cup, 2002 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship in Germany.
